======
RULES
======

(paint water cross from waterseed for trapdoors)

[ WaterSeed ] -> [ Basement RayU RayD RayL RayR ]
startloop
up    [ RayU | no Solid ] -> [ | RayU Basement ]
down  [ RayD | no Solid ] -> [ | RayD Basement ]
left  [ RayL | no Solid ] -> [ | RayL Basement ]
right [ RayR | no Solid ] -> [ | RayR Basement ]
endloop
late [ Rays ] -> []


(mirror rules)

[ > MirrorGuy ] [ Hint ] -> [ > MirrorGuy ] [ action Hint ]

[ CantMove ] -> []

late [ WaterAnim no Hole ] -> []

(Water anim)

(
[ stationary MirrorGuy ] [ stationary WaterAnim1 ] -> [ MirrorGuy] [ action WaterAnim2 ]
[ stationary MirrorGuy ] [ stationary WaterAnim2 ] -> [ MirrorGuy] [ action WaterAnim1 ]
)


(if there's a mirror on the map, replace background with mirrorbackground)

late [ Mirror ] [ HeroBackground ] -> [ Mirror ] [ MirrorBackground ]

late [ Mirror ] [ Goal ] -> [ Mirror ] [ Target ]

(Island border)


left  [ Mirror ] [ WaterHere no AddLandL | no WaterHere ] -> [ Mirror ] [ WaterHere AddLandLUD | ]
right [ Mirror ] [ WaterHere no AddLandR | no WaterHere ] -> [ Mirror ] [ WaterHere AddLandRUD | ]

up    [ Mirror ] [ AddLandLUD | WaterHere ] -> [ Mirror ] [ AddLandLD | WaterHere ]
up    [ Mirror ] [ AddLandRUD | WaterHere ] -> [ Mirror ] [ AddLandRD | WaterHere ]

down  [ Mirror ] [ AddLandLUD | WaterHere ] -> [ Mirror ] [ AddLandLU | WaterHere ]
down  [ Mirror ] [ AddLandRUD | WaterHere ] -> [ Mirror ] [ AddLandRU | WaterHere ]

down  [ Mirror ] [ AddLandLD | WaterHere ] -> [ Mirror ] [ | WaterHere ]
down  [ Mirror ] [ AddLandRD | WaterHere ] -> [ Mirror ] [ | WaterHere ]

left  [ Mirror ] [ no WaterHere no RemoveLandL | WaterHere ] -> [ Mirror ] [ RemoveLandLUD | WaterHere ]
right [ Mirror ] [ no WaterHere no RemoveLandR | WaterHere ] -> [ Mirror ] [ RemoveLandRUD | WaterHere ]

up    [ Mirror ] [ RemoveLandLUD | no WaterHere ] -> [ Mirror ] [ RemoveLandLD | ]
up    [ Mirror ] [ RemoveLandRUD | no WaterHere ] -> [ Mirror ] [ RemoveLandRD | ]

down  [ Mirror ] [ RemoveLandLUD | no WaterHere ] -> [ Mirror ] [ RemoveLandLU | ]
down  [ Mirror ] [ RemoveLandRUD | no WaterHere ] -> [ Mirror ] [ RemoveLandRU | ]

down  [ Mirror ] [ RemoveLandLD | no WaterHere ] -> [ Mirror ] [ | ]
down  [ Mirror ] [ RemoveLandRD | no WaterHere ] -> [ Mirror ] [ | ]


(Prevent teleport)

[ action MirrorGuy ] [ Reflection Hole ] -> [ action MirrorGuy ] [ CantMove Hole ]

[ CantMove ] [ action MirrorGuy ] -> [ CantMove ] [ MirrorGuy ] again

(Swap places)

(
[ action MirrorGuy HasReflection ] [ Reflection ] -> [ action MirrorGuy HasReflection ] [ Reflection MirrorGuy ]
[ Reflection MirrorGuy ] -> [ MirrorGuy ] sfx2
[ action MirrorGuy ] [ CrateReflection ] -> [ action MirrorGuy ] [ ReflectableCrate ] sfx2
[ action MirrorGuy ] [ ReflectableCrate HasReflection ] -> [ action MirrorGuy ] []
[ action MirrorGuy HasReflection ] -> [ Reflection ]
)

[ action MirrorGuy HasReflection ] [ Reflection ] -> [ action MirrorGuy HasReflection Teleported ] [ Reflection MirrorGuy ]
[ Reflection MirrorGuy ] -> [ MirrorGuy ] sfx2
[ action MirrorGuy ] [ CrateReflection ] -> [ action MirrorGuy Teleported ] [ ReflectableCrate ] sfx2
[ action MirrorGuy ] [ ReflectableCrate HasReflection ] -> [ action MirrorGuy Teleported ] []
[ action MirrorGuy HasReflection ] -> [ Reflection ]

(character switch only if NO teleport this tick)

[ Action MirrorGuy no Teleported ] [ SWizard ] -> [ SMirrorGuy ] [ Wizard Sfx1 ]
[ Action Wizard ] [ SMirrorGuy ] -> [ SWizard ] [ MirrorGuy Sfx1 ]

[ Action MirrorGuy no Teleported ] [ SMirrorGuy ] -> [ SMirrorGuy ] [ MirrorGuy Sfx1 ]

(cleanup)
[ Teleported ] -> []


(Clear state)

[ LOS ] -> []
[ HasReflection ] -> []
[ Reflection ] -> []
[ CrateReflection ] -> []

[ action MirrorGuy ] -> [ MirrorGuy ]

[ moving MirrorGuy ] -> [ moving MirrorGuy HasReflection ] (testing killing)

(Push things)

[ > MirrorGuy | Hole ] -> [ MirrorGuy | Hole ] sfx4

[ >  MirrorGuy | MirrorCrate | no Solid ] -> [  >  MirrorGuy | > MirrorCrate | ] sfx1
[ >  MirrorGuy | Mirror | no Solid ] -> [  >  MirrorGuy | > Mirror | ] sfx1 (allow pushing mirror into the hole)

[ > MirrorGuy | MirrorInHole ] -> [ MirrorGuy | MirrorInHole ] (stop mirrorguy from stepping on mirror in hole)

[ > MirrorGuy | stationary Mirror | Hole ] -> [ MirrorGuy | Mirror | Hole ] sfx4

[ >  MirrorGuy | MirrorCrate | > MirrorGuy ] -> [  >  MirrorGuy | > MirrorCrate | > MirrorGuy ] sfx1
[ >  MirrorGuy | Mirror | > MirrorGuy ] -> [  >  MirrorGuy | > Mirror | > MirrorGuy ] sfx1

([ > Mirror | Hole ] -> [ Mirror | Hole ] sfx4)

[ > Pushable | no Solid ] -> [ | Pushable ]
+ [ > MirrorGuy | no Solid ] -> [ | MirrorGuy ] sfx0

[ > MirrorGuy ] -> [ MirrorGuy ] sfx4

[ MirrorGuy Hole ] -> [ Hole ]

([ Mirror Hole ] -> cancel)

[ NormalCrate Hole ] -> [ CrateInHole ] sfx3
[ ReflectableCrate Hole ] -> [ CrateInHole ] sfx3
[ Mirror Hole ] -> [ MirrorInHole ] sfx3

[ MirrorGuy ] [ HasReflection ] -> [ MirrorGuy ] []

[ HasReflection ] -> cancel (all MirrorGuys dead)

(Make reflections)


startloop
random [ Reflectable no DirectionCounter ] -> [ action Reflectable North left 00 ]
+ [ Reflectable North ] -> [ action Reflectable East right 00 ]
+ [ Reflectable East ] -> [ action Reflectable South up 00 ]
+ [ Reflectable South ] -> [ action Reflectable West down 00 ]

[ > 00 | no Solid ] -> [ | > 01 LOS ]
[ > 01 | no Solid ] -> [ | > 02 LOS ]
[ > 02 | no Solid ] -> [ | > 03 LOS ]
[ > 03 | no Solid ] -> [ | > 04 LOS ]
[ > 04 | no Solid ] -> [ | > 05 LOS ]
[ > 05 | no Solid ] -> [ | > 06 LOS ]
[ > 06 | no Solid ] -> [ | > 07 LOS ]
[ > 07 | no Solid ] -> [ | > 08 LOS ]
[ > 08 | no Solid ] -> [ | > 09 LOS ]

[ > Counter | Solid no Mirror ] -> [ | Solid ]

left [ > Counter | MirrorUR ] -> [ | MirrorUR up Counter ]
+ left [ > Counter | MirrorDR ] -> [ | MirrorDR down Counter ]
+ right [ > Counter | MirrorUL ] -> [ | MirrorUL up Counter ]
+ right [ > Counter | MirrorDL ] -> [ | MirrorDL down Counter ]
+ up [ > Counter | MirrorDL ] -> [ | MirrorDL left Counter ]
+ up [ > Counter | MirrorDR ] -> [ | MirrorDR right Counter ]
+ down [ > Counter | MirrorUL ] -> [ | MirrorUL left Counter ]
+ down [ > Counter | MirrorUR ] -> [ | MirrorUR right Counter ]

+ [ > 09 | no Solid ] -> [ | > 08 LOS ]
+ [ > 08 | no Solid ] -> [ | > 07 LOS ]
+ [ > 07 | no Solid ] -> [ | > 06 LOS ]
+ [ > 06 | no Solid ] -> [ | > 05 LOS ]
+ [ > 05 | no Solid ] -> [ | > 04 LOS ]
+ [ > 04 | no Solid ] -> [ | > 03 LOS ]
+ [ > 03 | no Solid ] -> [ | > 02 LOS ]
+ [ > 02 | no Solid ] -> [ | > 01 LOS ]
+ [ > 01 | no Solid ] -> [ | > 00 LOS ]

[ > 00 | no Solid no CantMove ] [ action MirrorGuy ] -> [ | Reflection ] [ MirrorGuy HasReflection ]
[ > 00 | no Solid no CantMove ] [ action ReflectableCrate ] -> [ | CrateReflection ] [ ReflectableCrate HasReflection ]

[ Counter ] -> []

[ action Reflectable ] [ stationary LOS ] -> [ action Reflectable ] []

[ LOS ] -> [ action LOS ]

[ action Reflectable ] -> [ Reflectable ]
endloop


[ DirectionCounter ] -> []

[ stationary Hint ] [ ReflectableCrate HasReflection ] -> [] [ ReflectableCrate HasReflection ] message Oh the crates can reflect now. That is cool and totally not arbitrary

(hero rules)

([Saved] [Goal] -> [] [HasSavedDoor]) (Remembering whether we saved someone last round by temporarily changing some door to a HasSavedDoor. This is purely for sound effects purposes.)
(the rule above apparently breaks the compound goal+monsterdoor things in mosh_pit_small, so I commented it out)

[Corpse] -> Restart


[ > Fighter | Crate | PurpleDoor Basement ] -> [ > Fighter | | Basement CrateInHole] sfx3


[ >  Fighter | Moveable ] -> [  >  Fighter | > Moveable  ]

[ > Moveable | Moveable ] [ Fighter] -> [ > Moveable | > Moveable ] [ Fighter] (Fighters push.)

[ < Thief | Moveable ] -> [ < Thief | < Moveable ] (Thieves pull.)

[ > Wizard ] -> [ Wizard > Warpball]

(basement door rule added. check carefully. should work both with heroes1_21_v3 and dunk_tank_alt)

[ > Warpball | ClosedDoor Basement ] -> [ | ClosedDoor Basement > Warpball ]
+ [ > Warpball | no Moveable no Static ] -> [ | > Warpball ]

(continue wizard rules as usual)

[ > Warpball | Static] [Wizard] -> [ | Static ] [> Wizard]
[ > Warpball | Moveable ] [Wizard] -> [ | Wizard Sfx0] [Moveable]
[ > Warpball] [Wizard] -> [] [> Wizard]
(Wizards telexport. What they really do is shoot a "warpball", which causes them to move normally if it hits a wall or the edge of the screen and warp if it hits something they can warp with.)

(Druid does his thing. Warpball gets reused as a placeholder here. That's gonna happen a lot.)

[> Druid | Bush] -> [Druid | Crate Sfx8]
[> Druid | Crate] -> [Druid | Bush Sfx8]

[> Druid | Goblin] -> [Druid | FrozenGoblin Sfx8]
[> Druid | DragonUp] -> [Druid | FrozenDragonUp Sfx8]
[> Druid | DragonDown] -> [Druid | FrozenDragonDown Sfx8]
[> Druid | DragonLeft] -> [Druid | FrozenDragonLeft Sfx8]
[> Druid | DragonRight] -> [Druid | FrozenDragonRight Sfx8]

[> Druid | FrozenGoblin] -> [Druid | Goblin Sfx8]
[> Druid | FrozenDragonUp] -> [Druid | DragonUp Sfx8]
[> Druid | FrozenDragonDown] -> [Druid | DragonDown Sfx8]
[> Druid | FrozenDragonLeft] -> [Druid | DragonLeft Sfx8]
[> Druid | FrozenDragonRight] -> [Druid | DragonRight Sfx8]

[> Druid | Healer] -> [Druid | Healer Saved]
[> Druid | Hero] -> [Druid | Hero Warpball]
[Warpball | Healer] -> [Saved | Healer]
[Warpball Hero] -> [Wall Sfx8]
(What strategic purpose could it serve for healers to protect against petrification? None, but it's fun.)

(I mean, theoretically you could write some horrid dragon breath timing puzzle where the ability to delay an extra turn without moving or switching characters is necessary in order to let you move someone else at the correct moment, but even if dragons still existed, that sounds like a really gross level.)

(Bard moves stuff. Reusing "WarpBall" for totally different purpose, so we can cancel the move if he doesn't move.)

(
[> Bard no Note] -> [> Note > Bard WarpBall]
[> Note] [Note] -> [> Note] [> Note]
[> Note BardMoveable | no Static no BardMoveable no Bard] -> [| BardMoveable Sfx7]
+[> Note Bard WarpBall| no Static no BardMoveable no Bard] -> [| Bard]
)

[> Bard] -> [> Note > Bard WarpBall]
[> Note] [Note] -> [> Note] [> Note]

[ > Bard WarpBall | CrateInHole ] -> [ > Bard | CrateInHole ]

[> Note BardMoveable no CrateInHole | no Static no BardMoveable no Bard ] -> [| BardMoveable Sfx7]
+[> Note Bard WarpBall| no Static no BardMoveable no Bard no Hole] -> [| Bard]

[> Note Crate | Hole no Static no BardMoveable no Bard] -> [| CrateInHole Sfx7]
+[> Note Bard WarpBall| no Static no BardMoveable no Bard no Hole] -> [| Bard]

[> Note CrateInHole | WaterHere no Static no BardMoveable no Bard] -> [Hole WaterAnim1 | CrateInHole Sfx7]
+[> Note Bard WarpBall | no Static no BardMoveable no Bard no Hole] -> [| Bard]

[ > Bard | CrateInHole ] -> [ > Bard | CrateInHole ]


(Why are we doing this pseudo-movement instead of using the built-in version? Because using movement directions makes the note-adding stuff way easier below, and you can't use movement directions in the LATE phase, so the actual moving has to be done before then.)

[WarpBall] -> Cancel
[Note] -> []

(The following mess is for changing characters. But at least it's less messy than before. Thanks to Stephen for spotting my silly redundancies.)

[ Action Fighter] [SThief] -> [SFighter Switched] [Thief Sfx1]
[ Action Thief] [SWizard] -> [SThief] [Wizard Sfx1]
[ Action Wizard] [SPriest] -> [SWizard] [Priest Sfx1]
[ Action Priest] [SBard] -> [SPriest] [Bard Sfx1]
[ Action Bard] [SDruid] -> [SBard] [Druid Sfx1]
[ Action Druid] [SFighter] -> [SDruid] [Fighter Sfx1]

[ Action Fighter] [SWizard] -> [SFighter] [Wizard Sfx1]
[ Action Thief] [SPriest] -> [SThief] [Priest Sfx1]
[ Action Wizard] [SBard] -> [SWizard] [Bard Sfx1]
[ Action Priest] [SDruid] -> [SPriest] [Druid Sfx1]
[ Action Bard] [SFighter] -> [SBard] [Fighter Sfx1]
[ Action Druid] [SThief] -> [SDruid] [Thief Sfx1]

[ Action Fighter] [SPriest] -> [SFighter] [Priest Sfx1]
[ Action Thief] [SBard] -> [SThief] [Bard Sfx1]
[ Action Wizard] [SDruid] -> [SWizard] [Druid Sfx1]
[ Action Priest] [SFighter] -> [SPriest] [Fighter Sfx1]
[ Action Bard] [SThief] -> [SBard] [Thief Sfx1]
[ Action Druid] [SWizard] -> [SDruid] [Wizard Sfx1]

[ Action Fighter] [SBard] -> [SFighter] [Bard Sfx1]
[ Action Thief] [SDruid] -> [SThief] [Druid Sfx1]
[ Action Wizard] [SFighter] -> [SWizard] [Fighter Sfx1]
[ Action Priest] [SThief] -> [SPriest] [Thief Sfx1]
[ Action Bard] [SWizard] -> [SBard] [Wizard Sfx1]
[ Action Druid] [SPriest] -> [SDruid] [Priest Sfx1]

[ Action Fighter] [SDruid] -> [SFighter] [Druid Sfx1]
[ Action Thief] [SFighter] -> [SThief Switched] [Fighter Sfx1]
[ Action Wizard] [SThief] -> [SWizard] [Thief Sfx1]
[ Action Priest] [SWizard] -> [SPriest] [Wizard Sfx1]
[ Action Bard] [SPriest] -> [SBard] [Priest Sfx1]
[ Action Druid] [SBard] -> [SDruid] [Bard Sfx1]

[ Action Thief] [SThief] -> [SThief] [Thief Sfx1] (quadrants_follow_up)

(Bard plays music. This is my favorite part of the code, btw. Yes, you can make square area effects with just one object!)
[no Note | no Note | Bard] -> [^ Note | ^ Note | Bard]
[no Note | Bard] -> [^ Note | Bard]
[> Note | no Note | no Note] -> [Note | Note | Note]
[> Note | no Note] -> [Note | Note]
[> Note] -> [Note]

(Now enemies attack. Yeah, there's only one kind of enemy now.)

Late [Goblin | Vulnerable] -> [Goblin | Dying Vulnerable]

(Custom block about dragons and holes)

[ Switched ] [ DragonLeft ]  -> [ Switched ] [ DragonLeft Switched ]
Late [DragonLeft no Switched ] -> [LFireball DragonLeft] (prevent frying up the goblin in one_fire_v2 after character switching)
Late [DragonRight] -> [RFireball DragonRight]
Late RIGHT [RFireball | No Vulnerable no Invulnerable] -> [ | RFireball]
Late LEFT [LFireball | No Vulnerable no Invulnerable] -> [ | LFireball]
Late RIGHT [RFireball | Vulnerable] -> [ | Dying Vulnerable]
Late Right [RFireball | Invulnerable] -> [ | Invulnerable] 
Late Left [LFireball | Vulnerable] -> [ | Dying Vulnerable]
Late LEFT [LFireball | Invulnerable] -> [ | Invulnerable]

Late [DragonUp] -> [UFireball DragonUp]
Late [DragonDown] -> [DFireball DragonDown]
Late UP [UFireball | No Vulnerable no Invulnerable] -> [ | UFireball]
Late DOWN [DFireball | No Vulnerable no Invulnerable] -> [ | DFireball]
Late UP [UFireball | Vulnerable] -> [ | Dying Vulnerable]
Late Up [UFireball | Invulnerable] -> [ | Invulnerable] 
Late Down [DFireball | Vulnerable] -> [ | Dying Vulnerable]
Late DOWN [DFireball | Invulnerable] -> [ | Invulnerable]

[ > Hero | Hole ] -> [ Hero | Hole ]
late [ Crate Hole ] -> [ CrateInHole ] Sfx3
late [ Hole Vulnerable ] -> [ Hole Sfx5 ]

(Vulnerable objects that are attacked are designated as "Dying", but heroes can be saved by the Priest. Then the stuff that didn't get saved dies.)

Late [Dying Healer] -> [Saved Healer]
Late [Healer | Dying Hero] -> [Healer | Saved Hero]
Late [Dying Monster] -> [Sfx5]
Late [Dying Hero] -> [Corpse Sfx6]

(Doors opening.)

late [ColorDoor no DoorMarker no InvDoorMarker] -> [ColorDoor DoorMarker]
late [ColorOpen no DoorMarker no InvDoorMarker] -> [ColorOpen InvDoorMarker]

late [Weighing YellowSwitch] [YellowDoor DoorMarker] -> [Weighing YellowSwitch] [YellowOpen DoorMarker] Sfx3
late [YellowSwitch no Weighing] [YellowOpen DoorMarker] -> [YellowSwitch] [YellowDoor DoorMarker] Sfx2
late [Weighing YellowSwitch] [YellowOpen InvDoorMarker] -> [Weighing YellowSwitch] [YellowDoor InvDoorMarker] Sfx2
late [YellowSwitch no Weighing] [YellowDoor InvDoorMarker] -> [YellowSwitch] [YellowOpen InvDoorMarker] Sfx3

late [Weighing BlueSwitch] [BlueDoor DoorMarker] -> [Weighing BlueSwitch] [BlueOpen DoorMarker] Sfx3
late [BlueSwitch no Weighing] [BlueOpen DoorMarker Crate] -> [BlueSwitch] [CrateInHole DoorMarker]
late [BlueSwitch no Weighing] [BlueOpen DoorMarker no Crate] -> [BlueSwitch] [BlueDoor DoorMarker] Sfx2
late [Weighing BlueSwitch] [BlueOpen InvDoorMarker] -> [Weighing BlueSwitch] [BlueDoor InvDoorMarker] Sfx2
late [BlueSwitch no Weighing] [BlueDoor InvDoorMarker] -> [BlueSwitch] [BlueOpen InvDoorMarker] Sfx3

late [Weighing PurpleSwitch] [PurpleDoor DoorMarker] -> [Weighing PurpleSwitch] [PurpleOpen DoorMarker] Sfx3
late [PurpleSwitch no Weighing] [PurpleOpen DoorMarker Crate] -> [PurpleSwitch] [CrateInHole DoorMarker]
late [PurpleSwitch no Weighing] [PurpleOpen DoorMarker no Crate] -> [PurpleSwitch] [PurpleDoor DoorMarker] Sfx2
late [Weighing PurpleSwitch] [PurpleOpen InvDoorMarker] -> [Weighing PurpleSwitch] [PurpleDoor InvDoorMarker] Sfx2
late [PurpleSwitch no Weighing] [PurpleDoor InvDoorMarker] -> [PurpleSwitch] [PurpleOpen InvDoorMarker] Sfx3

late [Weighing GreenSwitch] [GreenDoor DoorMarker] -> [Weighing GreenSwitch] [GreenOpen DoorMarker] Sfx3
late [GreenSwitch no Weighing] [GreenOpen DoorMarker Crate] -> [GreenSwitch] [CrateInHole DoorMarker]
late [GreenSwitch no Weighing] [GreenOpen DoorMarker no Crate] -> [GreenSwitch] [GreenDoor DoorMarker] Sfx2
late [Weighing GreenSwitch] [GreenOpen InvDoorMarker] -> [Weighing GreenSwitch] [GreenDoor InvDoorMarker] Sfx2
late [GreenSwitch no Weighing] [GreenDoor InvDoorMarker] -> [GreenSwitch] [GreenOpen InvDoorMarker] Sfx3


(monster door)

late [MonsterDoor] -> [ShadowDoor]
late [ShadowDoor] [Monster] -> [MonsterDoor] [Monster]
late [ShadowDoor] -> [Sfx3]

(Looks for a HasSavedDoor and, if there is one, puts a warpball on the Priest. Then, if someone was saved this turn, plays the sound only if the Priest doesn't have the warpball. Finally, cleans that up.)

late [HasSavedDoor] [Healer] -> [Goal] [Healer WarpBall]
late [Saved] [Healer no WarpBall] -> [Saved Sfx4] [Healer]
late [HasSavedDoor] -> [Goal]
late [WarpBall] -> []

late [Note no BardMoveable] -> []

late [Saved no Hero] -> [] (NB! removes cross from non-hero cells. re-check if truly works)


late [Switched] -> []


(very late rules, assign sprites to doors, swap visual representation for basement doors)

late [ Basement no WaterAnim1 ] -> [ Basement WaterAnim1]


late [ YellowDoor Basement ] -> [ YellowDoor YellowOpenA Basement ]
late [ YellowOpen Basement ] -> [ YellowOpen YellowDoorA Basement ]

late [ PurpleDoor Basement ] -> [ PurpleDoor PurpleOpenA Basement ]
late [ PurpleOpen Basement ] -> [ PurpleOpen PurpleDoorA Basement ]


late [ BlueDoor Basement ] -> [ BlueDoor BlueOpenA Basement ]
late [ BlueOpen Basement ] -> [ BlueOpen BlueDoorA Basement ]

late [ GreenDoor Basement ] -> [ GreenDoor GreenOpenA Basement ]
late [ GreenOpen Basement ] -> [ GreenOpen GreenDoorA Basement ]


late [ YellowDoor no Basement ] -> [ YellowDoor YellowDoorA ]
late [ YellowOpen no Basement ] -> [ YellowOpen YellowOpenA ]

late [ PurpleDoor no Basement ] -> [ PurpleDoor PurpleDoorA ]
late [ PurpleOpen no Basement ] -> [ PurpleOpen PurpleOpenA ]

late [ BlueDoor no Basement ] -> [ BlueDoor BlueDoorA ]
late [ BlueOpen no Basement ] -> [ BlueOpen BlueOpenA ]

late [ GreenDoor no Basement ] -> [ GreenDoor GreenDoorA ]
late [ GreenOpen no Basement ] -> [ GreenOpen GreenOpenA ]


